tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1693:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1720:        "name": "mutation-strength",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1730:          "mutation"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1733:        "body": "Test suites are gated on mutation strength via `cargo-mutants`. Surviving mutants are treated as evidence of weak scenarios: each survivor must be triaged and resolved against a behavior ID (`BEH-*`) — either by tightening an existing scenario, adding a falsification scenario, or explicitly recording the mutant as equivalent with a linked justification. Mutation regressions fail the final gate; the staged `just` recipes surface mutant output in a machine-consumable form for triage."
